Calum Chambers, Eric Dier and John Stones have all impressed this season . 
  Arsenal defender Chambers has played at right back, centre-back and midfield for the Gunners . 
  Everton defender Stones has moved from right back to centre back for the Toffees . 
  Tottenham defender Dier has impressed in his first season at the club . 
  Roy Hodgson could play the trio in a back three for England . 
 